{
  "stem": "1502.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There were Jewish Communist Party, Jewish Socialist Party.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There was all the Zionist Party, the Revisionists, the Liberals, the Leftists, you name it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was a very rich Jewish cultural life, even there were only about 60,000 or 65,000 Jews in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But they were very tight knit, and there was a lot of Jewish activity.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There was a Jewish theatre.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "There was a-- there was a strong Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "There were relief organizations.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And everything started to function again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Not at the same strength, because certain Jews fled to France on time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they remained in southern France.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they wouldn't come back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So from the Jews that remained in Belgium, I wouldn't say what percentage, but maybe 20% of Jews never came back to the-- to the German occupation, because they were on the other side.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Some of them reached Spain, and Portugal, United States, or Palestine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And those people that-- the majority that remained in-- in Belgium, as I said, life was normal for about a year.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "After a year, they came out with the first anti-Jewish laws, which were, in the beginning, mild, like Jews are not allowed to have a business.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So the Jews that had small businesses, they had to liquidate the business and send all the remaining merchandise to a certain office, which they named where to ship, and apparently will be paid.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And the larger Jewish businesses, they installed what they called a commissioner, a German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They would put the German, and he was running the business.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And actually, with the time, he took over the business and threw out the Jewish owners without compensation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But that was the-- that was the beginning.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
